    local deckIndexString = string.sub(message, 12)
    local deckIndex = tonumber(deckIndexString)

    if deckIndex != nil then
      if ((deckIndex >= 1) and (deckIndex <= #deckData)) then
        parseDeckString(chatPlayer.color, deckIndex, deckData[deckIndex].deckString, true, false, true)

function checkAllDecks()
  local numDecksPassed = 0
  local numCardsSupported = 0
  local numDecks = 0

  for deckIndex,curDeckData in ipairs(deckData) do
    numCardsSupported = parseDeckString("White", deckIndex, curDeckData.deckString, false, true, false)
    if numCardsSupported == 36 then
      printToAll(deckIndex .. ".   " .. curDeckData.deckName, {0,0.7,0})
      numDecksPassed = numDecksPassed + 1
    else
      printToAll(deckIndex .. ".   " .. curDeckData.deckName .. "   (" .. numCardsSupported .. "/36)", {1,0,0})
    end

    numDecks = numDecks + 1
  end

  printToAll("Number of decks passed:  " .. numDecksPassed .. "/" .. numDecks, {1,1,1})
end


function getHouseString(houseCode)
  local returnString = nil

  if houseCode == 'B' then
    returnString = "Brobnar"
  elseif houseCode == 'L' then
    returnString = "Logos"
  elseif houseCode == 'H' then
    returnString = "Shadows"
  elseif houseCode == 'S' then
    returnString = "Sanctum"
  elseif houseCode == 'M' then
    returnString = "Mars"
  elseif houseCode == 'D' then
    returnString = "Dis"
  elseif houseCode == 'U' then
    returnString = "Untamed"
  else
    returnString = nil
  end

  return returnString
end

function isMaverick(houseString, cardNumberString)
  local numberRange = houseNumberRanges[houseString]
  local retValue = false
  local cardNumber = tonumber(cardNumberString)

  -- Check if the number is outside its expected range.
  if ((cardNumber < numberRange[1]) or (cardNumber > numberRange[2])) then
    retValue = true
  end

  return retValue
end

function parseDeckString(playerColor, deckIndex, deckString, shouldSpawn, shouldBeSilent, shouldShuffle)
  local isDeckValid = true
  local curSegmentIndex = 1
  local curCardIndex = 1
  local curHouseIndex = 1
  local curHouseString = nil
  local segments = {}
  local deckName = nil
  local houseStrings = {}
  local cardNumbers = {{}, {}, {}}
  local numCardsSupported = 0
  local curCardNumberString = false
  local curCardFound = false

  curSegmentIndex = 1
  for curSegment in string.gmatch(deckString, "[^~]+") do
    segments[curSegmentIndex] = curSegment
    curSegmentIndex = (curSegmentIndex + 1)
  end

  if curSegmentIndex == 6 then
    deckName = segments[1]

    curHouseIndex = 1
    for curHouseCode in string.gmatch(segments[2], "[A-Z]") do
      houseStrings[curHouseIndex] = getHouseString(curHouseCode)
      curHouseIndex = (curHouseIndex + 1)
    end

    if ((houseStrings[1] == nil) or
        (houseStrings[2] == nil) or
        (houseStrings[3] == nil)) then
      isDeckValid = false
    end
  end

  if isDeckValid == true then
    for curHouseIndex=1,3 do
      curHouseString = houseStrings[curHouseIndex]
      curCardIndex = 1
      for curCardNumberString in string.gmatch(segments[2 + curHouseIndex], "[0-9]+") do
        if isMaverick(curHouseString, curCardNumberString) then
          -- Append the house since this card is a maverick.
          cardNumbers[curHouseIndex][curCardIndex] = (curCardNumberString .. " " .. curHouseString)
        else
          cardNumbers[curHouseIndex][curCardIndex] = curCardNumberString
        end
        curCardIndex = (curCardIndex + 1)
      end
    end
  end

  if isDeckValid == true then
    if shouldBeSilent == false then
      printToAll("", {1,1,1})
      printToAll("DECK:  " .. deckName .. "  (#" .. deckIndex .. ")", {1,1,1})
      printToAll("", {1,1,1})
      printToAll("FACTIONS:  " .. houseStrings[1] .. " / " .. houseStrings[2] .. " / " .. houseStrings[3], {1,1,1})
      printToAll("", {1,1,1})
    end

    for curHouseIndex=1,3 do
      for curCardIndex=1,12 do
        curCardNumberString = cardNumbers[curHouseIndex][curCardIndex]
        curCardFound = false

        for checkIndex,curData in ipairs(cardImageData) do
          if curData.number == curCardNumberString then
            -- Check whether the card has a known card sheet.
            if curData.deckid != 0 then
              numCardsSupported = (numCardsSupported + 1)
            else
              if shouldBeSilent == false then
                printToAll("Card number " .. curCardNumberString .. " not yet supported in this mod.", {1,0,0})
              end
            end

            curCardFound = true
            break
          end
        end

        if curCardFound == false then
          if shouldBeSilent == false then
            printToAll("Card number " .. curCardNumberString .. " is invalid.", {1,0,0})
          end
        end
      end
    end

    if shouldBeSilent == false then
      if numCardsSupported == 36 then
        printToAll("Deck check passed.", {1,1,1})

        if shouldSpawn == true then
          printToAll("Spawning deck...", {1,1,1})
          spawnDeck(playerColor, deckIndex, deckName, houseStrings, cardNumbers, shouldShuffle)
        end
      else
        printToAll("Deck not yet usable in this mod, only " .. numCardsSupported .. "/36 cards supported.", {1,0,0})
      end
    end
  else
    if shouldBeSilent == false then
      printToAll("", {1,1,1})
      printToAll("Invalid deck string.", {1,1,1})
      printToAll("", {1,1,1})
    end
  end

  return numCardsSupported
end


function spawnDeck(playerColor, deckIndex, deckName, houseStrings, cardNumbers, shouldShuffle)
  local curHouse = nil
  local spawnCardNumberString = nil
  local spawnCardIndex = 1

  for curHouseIndex=1,3 do
    curHouse = houseStrings[curHouseIndex]
    for cardIndex,curCardNumberString in ipairs(cardNumbers[curHouseIndex]) do
      for checkIndex,checkCardData in ipairs(cardData) do
        if checkCardData.number == curCardNumberString then
          spawnCardNumberString = curCardNumberString
          if (checkCardData.house != curHouse) then
            -- Append the house since this card is a maverick.
            spawnCardNumberString = (spawnCardNumberString .. " " .. curHouse)
          end

          spawnCard(playerColor, spawnCardNumberString, checkCardData, (2.0 + (spawnCardIndex * 0.3)), shouldShuffle)
          spawnCardIndex = spawnCardIndex + 1
          break
        end
      end
    end
  end

  if playerColor == "White" then
    if shouldShuffle == true then
      utilityZoneWhite.setPosition({ 0.00, 3.00, -6.25 })
    else
      utilityZoneWhite.setPosition({ 32.00, 3.00, -6.25 })
    end
  else
    if shouldShuffle == true then
      utilityZoneBlue.setPosition({ 0.00, 3.00, 6.25 })
    else
      utilityZoneBlue.setPosition({ 32.00, 3.00, 6.25 })
    end
  end

  Wait.time(function() finishDeckSpawn(playerColor, deckIndex, deckName, shouldShuffle) end, 1.7)
end


function spawnCard(playerColor, spawnCardNumberString, spawnCardData, spawnHeight, shouldShuffle)
  local spawnCardImageData = nil
  local spawnFaceURL = nil
  local spawnDeckID = nil
  local spawnNumHeight = nil
  local spawnParams = {}

  for checkIndex,curData in ipairs(cardImageData) do
    if curData.number == spawnCardNumberString then
      spawnCardImageData = curData
      spawnDeckID = spawnCardImageData.deckid
      spawnFaceURL = cardSheetData[spawnDeckID].url
      spawnNumHeight = cardSheetData[spawnDeckID].numHeight
      break
    end
  end

  if spawnDeckID != nil then
    cardTemplateJSON.CardID = spawnCardImageData.cardid
    cardTemplateJSON.Nickname = spawnCardData.name
    cardTemplateJSON.Description = spawnCardData.number
    -- Reset the custom deck each time this function is called, just in case it is best to reinitialize.
    cardTemplateJSON.CustomDeck = nil
    cardTemplateJSON.CustomDeck = {}
    --print(cardTemplateJSON.CardID .. "     " .. spawnDeckID .. "     " .. spawnFaceURL)
    cardTemplateJSON.CustomDeck[tostring(spawnDeckID)] = {
      FaceURL = spawnFaceURL,
      BackURL = "http://drive.google.com/uc?id=199D6-iUYgUj2uRfhAvYWBUOQ4QnuhapN",
      NumWidth = 10,
      NumHeight = spawnNumHeight,
      BackIsHidden = true,
      UniqueBack = false
    }

    spawnParams.json = JSON.encode(cardTemplateJSON)

    if playerColor == "White" then
      if shouldShuffle == true then
        spawnParams.position = { 0, spawnHeight, -6.25 }
      else
        spawnParams.position = { 32, spawnHeight, -6.25 }
      end

      spawnParams.rotation = { 0, 180, 180 }
    else
      if shouldShuffle == true then
        spawnParams.position = { 0, spawnHeight, 6.25 }
      else
        spawnParams.position = { 32, spawnHeight, 6.25 }
      end

      spawnParams.rotation = { 0, 0, 180 }
    end

    spawnObjectJSON(spawnParams)
  else
    -- This should never happen.
    printToAll("Error, failed to find card sheet data for card " .. spawnCardNumberString .. ".", {1,0,0})
  end
end


function finishDeckSpawn(playerColor, deckIndex, deckName, shouldShuffle)
  local scriptZoneObjects = nil
  local spawnedDeck = nil
  local deckNameWithNumber = nil
  local chainCount = 0

  if shouldShuffle == true then
    printToAll("Shuffling deck...", {1,1,1})
  end

  if playerColor == "White" then
    scriptZoneObjects = utilityZoneWhite.getObjects()
  elseif playerColor == "Blue" then
    scriptZoneObjects = utilityZoneBlue.getObjects()
  end

  for deckIndex,curDeck in ipairs(scriptZoneObjects) do
    if curDeck.tag == "Deck" then
      spawnedDeck = curDeck
      break
    end
  end

  if spawnedDeck != nil then
    deckNameWithNumber = deckName .. "  (#" .. deckIndex.. ")"
    spawnedDeck.setName(deckNameWithNumber)
    if shouldShuffle == true then
      spawnedDeck.shuffle()
      spawnedDeck.shuffle()
      spawnedDeck.shuffle()
    end

    chainCount = deckChains[deckIndex]
    if chainCount != nil then
      printToAll("WARNING:  This is a strong deck.  " .. chainCount .. " chains are recommended to start.", {1,0,0})

      -- TODO add support for other numbers of starting chains
      if playerColor == "White" then
        if chainCount == 2 then
          chainCubeWhite.setPosition({ 14.68, 1.86, -11.35 })
        else
          printToAll("Error, unsupported number of starting chains.", {1,0,0})
        end
      else
        if chainCount == 2 then
          chainCubeBlue.setPosition({ -14.68, 1.86, 11.35 })
        else
          printToAll("Error, unsupported number of starting chains.", {1,0,0})
        end
      end
    end

    Wait.time(function() printToAll("Done.", {1,1,1}) end, 0.8)
  else
    printToAll("Error, failed to find spawned deck.", {1,0,0})
  end
end
